DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: White Shark has always been more than a place, a corporation, a collective.
White shark is an idea, it's the dream of a great man.
With the aid of his technology and our Great White as a vessel we sailed across the sea and into the future.
Thanks to our advanced level of security, we have been able to keep safe secrets from every country at times of war, managing to keep peace between them.
We have the most advanced equipment and the most qualified individuals working together to make the dream of our Founder a reality.

But all that glitters is not gold, and White Shark is no exception. Most of our technology was made at the expense of people who will never see the light of day. Who will work without even having a purpose… or a choice.
The Belly, the slums. The residential common area, the home of the little people, as the snobs like to call them.
Our founder was smart. He managed to find a way to channel and generate emotions. To control people through chemistry and electric pulses.
What he could not predict is that after generations some of us would indeed evolve, but to be able to resist him better… and that’s where everything started.
Strange murders started occurring, most of them related to those who dared resisting. Their brains gone and their murderers amnesics.
People began to grow frightened. They no longer felt safe even with the aid of their bracelet.
After a few failed tries to solve the mystery a foreigner was asked for help. An expert from a neutral country. An outsider.
This is where things got complicated, and you’ll soon understand why.
I’m doctor Alexia Ross, head of the detective program, and I will tell you the story of White Shark.
That way those who had the reasons to rebel wouldn’t want to; and the ones who could were too happy to think about it.
To assuage the peoples' fears, White Shark founded a detective division.
Here thousands of people are forced to spend every day of their lives toiling away, not even able to imagine a life of comfort like those above. In the Fin.
A great man who was able to envision a future for mankind which advanced us down the path toward the next evolutionary step.
We have to go! What’s taking so long?
